sql:
SELECT job_id, AVG(precision_score_value) AS avg_precision_score
FROM precision_score
GROUP BY job_id;

SELECT precision_score_value, epoch
FROM precision_score
WHERE precision_score_value > 0.8;

external_knowledge:
- In this context, a loss value below 0.5 likely indicates a better-performing model or job; 
- A time value above 20 seconds may signify computationally expensive jobs; 
- Research teams and their performance might be compared or ranked based on these metrics.

External knowledge:
- F1 score is a measure of a model's accuracy on a specific task, with higher values indicating better performance;
- The epoch with the highest F1 score value represents the point at which the model performed best.

sql:
SELECT epoch
FROM f1_score
WHERE f1_score_value = (SELECT MAX(f1_score_value) FROM f1_score);

external_knowledge:
- "matured under the watchful eye of AWS" refers to models trained on the AWS cloud provider; 
- "walked the path of hardware configuration 1" refers to models trained using hardware configuration 1; 
- "achieved wisdom" refers to models that have completed their training jobs; 
- "average validation loss score below 0.7" refers to models with an average validation loss value less than 0.7, indicating better performance.

sql:
SELECT val_loss_id
FROM val_loss
WHERE val_loss_value > 0.5;

SELECT AVG(loss_value) AS average_loss
FROM losses
WHERE epoch > 10;

SELECT loss_value
     FROM losses
     WHERE loss_value > 0.45;

SELECT hardware_name
FROM hardware_configurations
ORDER BY created_at DESC;
